-- Turkish deputy PM wants state banks to own Islamic lenders -TV
-- By Ece Toksabay
-- Wed Aug 06, 2014 06:31AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Aug 6 (Reuters) - Turkish Deputy Prime Minister Ali Babacan said on Wednesday the government wanted state banks Ziraat, Halkbank <HALKB.IS> and Vakifbank <VAKBN.IS> to own Islamic lenders and that Ziraat would own an Islamic lender if it bought Bank Asya <ASYAB.IS>.

